A Ranunculus fascicularis is a flowering herbaceous plant that belongs to the buttercup family. 

It has a bright yellow, five-petaled flower with a shiny, waxy texture and a cup-shaped form. 

The leaves of the Ranunculus fascicularis are primarily basal and deeply lobed. 

This plant thrives in damp or wet soil and can often be found in meadows, along stream banks, or in other wetland habitats. 

Ranunculus fascicularis is often used as a garden plant or in horticultural displays due to its beautiful flowers. 

The stem of the Ranunculus fascicularis can reach up to 18 inches in height and the plant generally blooms in the spring and early summer. 

Overall, the visual characteristics of a Ranunculus fascicularis are bright, sunny, and lively.
